{
  "stem": "1858.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I said, we would come from work tired, exhausted, hungry, cold.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We would be called to [NON-ENGLISH], roll call, where we would be forced to stand outdoors in all kinds of weather, and wonder what our Nazi guards were doing to us.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When it was snowing, they would tell us to lay flat in the snow and crawl.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had no warm clothing on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Do you know what happens to hands, to knees, when you lay in the snow?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Or when it poured, they told us to make long lines all the way from one end to the other.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they told us to either use little pails or drinking cups, scoop up water from each puddle, pass it down the line, and pour it beyond the fence.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Do you know what happens to a puddle of water when it rains?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You scoop out the water and it fills up again.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Our passport to life really was work.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As long as you could produce, you were allowed to live.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The minute you became too weak or too sick, you were done away with.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But this no longer was work to produce, this was work to humiliate and degrade us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "From time to time, they would tell us to remove our uniform and stand there in the nude.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They called it bodily inspection.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't believe that the guards-- the main guards in particular-- did this to look at us females.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because, by that time, we resembled anything but females.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was nothing left on our bodies but skin and bone.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't think that we could appeal to a man as a female.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But just think what it did to our own person, standing there and viewing each other totally naked, totally helpless, totally powerless, so degraded.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
